Title: Bike Boxes City of Madison, WI 2018
Description: This data layer represents bike boxes for the City of Madison, Wisconsin in 2018. A bike box is a designated area at the head of a traffic lane at a signalized intersection that provides bicyclists with a safe and visible way to get ahead of queuing traffic during the red signal phase.
Originator: City of Madison - Metropolitan Planning Organization (MPO)
